SIMPLE: commensal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Commensal
<hw>Com*men"sal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>commensalis</ets>; L. <ets>com-</ets> + <ets>mensa</ets> table: cf.
F. <ets>commensal</ets>. Cf. Mensal.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
eats at the same table.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An animal, not truly parasitic,
which lives in, with, or on, another, partaking usually of the same
food. Both species may be benefited by the association.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commensal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Commensal
<hw>Com*men"sal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the
character of a commensal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commensalism</ent>⟦br⟧
